                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d54">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.H Agenda/251: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hull</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-12-16T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 16, 1938—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>57. Relative to Mexican project respecting Aerial Bombardments, Navy Department
                    states it does not object to the general proposal, but expresses its own view
                    that, in absence of military or naval advisers to United States delegation,
                    projects “affecting military operations be not considered at the present
                    Conference”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
